latestPosts.caption: 📍Six Seven is a beautiful waterfront restaurant inside The Edgewater Hotel right on Elliott Bay. It’s known for fresh PNW seafood, sunset views, and its cozy dining room that sits over the water. Great spot for brunch or a special dinner in Seattle.

Some days, I walk slower, not because I’m tired, but because seattle deserves to be noticed.

🌇👣 @joncmlife #seattlewashington

Do you have friends visiting Seattle this summer? Save this one-day itinerary to show them four iconic spots at @mountrainiernps 🏔️🥾✨

1️⃣ Start at the Sunrise Visitor Center and hike to Mount Fremont Fire Lookout. This trail is 5.7 miles round-trip with 1,100 feet of elevation gain and is perfect for anyone new to hiking in Washington. We ate lunch at the lookout and even got to see some mountain goats! 

2️⃣ Drive to the Paradise Corridor of the park using the Stevens Canyon Entrance. Stop at Reflection Lake. 

3️⃣ Continue the drive all the way up to the visitor center. Walk to Myrtle Falls (about a half mile from the parking lot) and explore a small portion of the Skyline Loop. 

4️⃣ Stop at Narada Falls as you start the drive back to Seattle. The lower viewpoint is a 0.2-mile hike from the parking lot. 

🚗 This itinerary requires a LOT of driving but there are so many additional stops you could make to break it up (plus the views along the way are stunning!!)

⏰ Timed entry reservations are required for the Sunrise Corridor from 7am to 5pm starting July 11th. There are no reservations required for the Paradise Corridor this summer.

⚠️ Always check weather reports and trail conditions before heading out and remember to leave no trace.

✈️This is NOT Provence, France. This is not even in Europe.
📍This is Washington (🪻+ 🏔️)
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW adventures for busy people @adventuresoncall
.
☀️ Did you know that lavender is a huge industry in Washington, even though lavender likes very dry, hot weather?
.
💜The PNW is infamous for rain, but there are unique microclimates (mild winters, low precipitation, abundant sunshine) which is perfect for lavender cultivation. In fact, Sequim is the Lavender Capital of North America
.
🪻Peak Lavender blooming season is now! Blooms are late June through early August
🪻 This year’s Sequim Lavender Festival is July 18 - July 20, 2025 (Personally I prefer other days for less crowds)
🪻 Places to find lavender farms include Sequim, Whidbey Island, Ferndale, Olympia, and Woodinville
🪻Sequim Lavender Trail is a scenic driving / cycling route on a tour of the lavender farms in Sequim open all summer long.
🪻Check for U-pick and dog friendly options (many are dog friendly)! 🐾
🪻 Many lavender farms have stores open all year - highly recommend trying lavender ice cream, lavender lemonade, lavender jam, lavender soaps/lotions, and more 🍦
.
🏔️And you can get lavender + Mt Rainier views on a clear day
.
.

𝗪𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗴𝗼𝗹𝗱𝗲𝗻 𝗵𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗵𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗡𝗲𝗲𝗱𝗹𝗲... 𝗶𝘁 𝗵𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝘁.
Seattle just snapped and said: “Hold my coffee.”
⁣
Up here, the city doesn’t sleep — it exhales.
Sunbeams kissing glass, rooftops glowing, the sky melting into the Sound…
⁣
📍That moment when you’re floating above the 206, and for a split second, nothing else matters.
⁣
This ain’t just a view — it’s a vibe.
⁣
💭 Ever watched the sun set on a city that’s still dreaming big?
This is it. And yes, it’s every bit as unreal as it looks.

👇🏼
